"},{"source":"recnP1NhXroEtZCXx","target":"recfrXyxhuYOczKTm","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recnP1NhXroEtZCXx","target":"recvDlppuKNnN5srC","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recnP1NhXroEtZCXx","target":"rec1tleh7fR8tsqKa","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recnP1NhXroEtZCXx","target":"recDNxYH4BhZWW7rS","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recnP1NhXroEtZCXx","target":"recoBlOCXvzVsT1pS","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recnP1NhXroEtZCXx","target":"recVHSiFLmbUrZHLJ","label":"mentions"}],"verses":[{"id":"recFlMDSrdSOh9Yez","ref":"Gen.26.1","text":"And there was a famine in the land, beside the first famine that was in the days of Abraham. And Isaac went unto Abimelech king of the Philistines unto Gerar.","year":-1804},{"id":"recSZhu9gurNV6ASs","ref":"Gen.26.2","text":"And the LORD appeared unto him, and said, Go not down into Egypt; dwell in the land which I shall tell thee of:","year":-1804},{"id":"recGQAyVuOuW8iVRX","ref":"Gen.26.3","text":"Sojourn in this land, and I will be with thee, and will bless thee; for unto thee, and unto thy seed, I will give all these countries, and I will perform the oath which I sware unto Abraham thy father;","year":-1804},{"id":"recAenBTcpL2E1IQC","ref":"Gen.26.4","text":"And I will make thy seed to multiply as the stars of heaven, and will give unto thy seed all these countries; and in thy seed shall all the nations of the earth be blessed;","year":-1804},{"id":"recHuGb9CqzJA4JkB","ref":"Gen.26.5","text":"Because that Abraham obeyed my voice, and kept my charge, my commandments, my statutes, and my laws.","year":-1804},{"id":"recEOEbZRLpLe1wVA","ref":"Gen.26.6","text":"And Isaac dwelt in Gerar:","year":-1804},{"id":"recLtvkyktwUbhqbO","ref":"Gen.26.7","text":"And the men of the place asked him of his wife; and he said, She is my sister: for he feared to say, She is my wife; lest, said he, the men of the place should kill me for Rebekah; because she was fair to look upon.","year":-1804},{"id":"recCql1Rug3srs32H","ref":"Gen.26.8","text":"And it came to pass, when he had been there a long time, that Abimelech king of the Philistines looked out at a window, and saw, and, behold, Isaac was sporting with Rebekah his wife.","year":-1804}]}
